	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98472218077293><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=98472218077293>RE: Wizards, the Nerf class</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=98472218077293#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 16th 12:56 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This may be alittle off the subject but the way the game was supossed to be designed, each class and race has its pluses and minus. Wiz are the complete opposite of Wars, all magic no melee. I play a lv 34 war and personally I just dont have the patience for mana and magic. What is great about this game is that there is a variety of ways to play the game personafied by each of the classes. Want to solo? Be a druid or a necro. More a of social person? Be an enchanter, a wiz or a tank if you like. The point is to have fun with it and dont expect too much from your class and race. The Wiz is the typical 98lbs weakling but can nuke for a hell of alot of hp, Evac has saved my war's and groups arse many times and frankly tp'ing is great money for mana. Find the class and race that is right for you and have fun with it. Is the true name of this game :)<br>Hammers judge ye kindly<br>Valhalan Rothgarr&lt;Avenging Storm&gt;<br>Lv 34 War in service to the Tribunal<br>7th Hammer<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
