<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=98821841280894></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98821841280894><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=98821841280894>RE: Wizards, the Nerf class</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=98821841280894#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 25th 1:06 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think that the problems that most people have with wizards are strictly post-50.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm a level 55 now (almost to 56) and really had no complaints until recently.  <br><br>The upgrades to the damage spells are not reflective of the higher level.  For instance, Draught of Fire (level 51 ManaEfficient DD) will do the exact same damage as Vol. Draught (55).  This is because of the increase in damage continues for draught of fire beyond level 55.  The only difference is whether you are casting against Fire resists or Magic resists.  Not a real good increase for gaining 4 levels. <br><br>I love playing a wizard, but i do believe that Verant needs to take a bit of a look at the higher level spells or perhaps just tweak our mana recovery rate a touch.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
